{
  "text": "The potential solutions for such problems may be: (i) the development of advanced software for spectral search methods, which can result in greater sensitivity and more accuracy in the search for the MPs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , (ii) a combined solubilization method for the initial sample treatment step [CITATION_4] ; among the reagents, sodium deoxycholate and RapiGest showed good solubility and enzyme compatibility as well as easy removal in later steps prior to the MS analysis; (iii) the use of high-resolution mass spectrometry; and (iv) the use of RNA Seq analysis to better guide tissue selection and timing and to identify tissues or cells not commonly used for MS analyses [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] ( Table 1 ). In particular for PE2 proteins, C-HPP investigators can approach to perform target proteomics in order to identify PE2 class MPs by utilizing genomics dataset (e.g., RNA-seq) obtained from some specific tissues or cell lines [CITATION_8] . Duek et al., attempted to detect MPs from testis by analyzing RNA-seq data and proteomic profiling with MRM assays [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] .",
